1
00:00:22,464 --> 00:00:26,432
♪Should we forget yesterday's sorrows♪

2
00:00:26,432 --> 00:00:29,728
♪And the dazed confusion♪

3
00:00:30,976 --> 00:00:33,681
♪Should we let go of♪

4
00:00:33,681 --> 00:00:35,904
♪The stubborn madness♪

5
00:00:35,904 --> 00:00:39,072
♪And naive recklessness now♪

6
00:00:40,192 --> 00:00:43,840
♪Those years, those faces♪

7
00:00:44,992 --> 00:00:48,763
♪Those old scars we can't erase♪

8
00:00:49,824 --> 00:00:52,460
♪Tears streaming, facing the light♪

9
00:00:53,152 --> 00:00:57,594
♪Piercing the sorrow within♪

10
00:01:08,716 --> 00:01:12,736
♪The road ahead's long,
stumbling all the way♪

11
00:01:13,536 --> 00:01:18,076
♪The wounds we've borne
are medals hidden within♪

12
00:01:18,336 --> 00:01:22,391
♪Standing alone on an open plain♪

13
00:01:23,168 --> 00:01:26,851
♪We gaze at the stars♪

14
00:01:31,228 --> 00:01:34,816
=The Dream Maker=

15
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,880
=Episode 39=

16
00:01:38,424 --> 00:01:39,344
I don't know expansion.

17
00:01:39,825 --> 00:01:41,784
I don't know if it'll succeed either.

18
00:01:42,584 --> 00:01:44,545
But I know Mr. Zheng and Ms. Li

19
00:01:45,048 --> 00:01:45,625
well.

20
00:01:46,825 --> 00:01:47,424
I trust them.

21
00:01:49,504 --> 00:01:50,944
Ms. Gao certainly has courage!

22
00:01:51,185 --> 00:01:51,784
Yes.

23
00:01:52,224 --> 00:01:52,745
Ms. Gao,

24
00:01:53,144 --> 00:01:54,224
your business is huge,

25
00:01:54,504 --> 00:01:56,784
but here we have
over 30 people with over 50 plots.

26
00:01:57,064 --> 00:01:57,985
Do you have that much?

27
00:01:58,224 --> 00:01:59,584
None of your business.

28
00:01:59,985 --> 00:02:00,905
Today, I'll first

29
00:02:00,905 --> 00:02:02,504
take those three storefronts of yours.

30
00:02:08,545 --> 00:02:09,545
I've made up my mind.

31
00:02:10,545 --> 00:02:11,385
I don't want to sign

32
00:02:13,265 --> 00:02:14,264
either of the contracts.

33
00:02:15,584 --> 00:02:16,424
Now, down south,

34
00:02:16,505 --> 00:02:17,545
real estate is profitable.

35
00:02:17,665 --> 00:02:18,744
It's got huge potential.

36
00:02:18,945 --> 00:02:19,864
I'd like a gamble.

37
00:02:21,665 --> 00:02:22,184
Xuemei,

38
00:02:22,785 --> 00:02:24,424
I will cover the losses with you.

39
00:02:28,464 --> 00:02:29,545
One thing I want to change:

40
00:02:30,065 --> 00:02:31,345
The money won't take a month.

41
00:02:31,945 --> 00:02:32,624
I'll take

42
00:02:32,665 --> 00:02:33,985
any shops you want to sell.

43
00:02:34,704 --> 00:02:35,345
Right now,

44
00:02:35,785 --> 00:02:36,904
I'll write you checks here.

45
00:02:39,105 --> 00:02:40,144
Have you lost your mind?

46
00:02:43,505 --> 00:02:44,065
Come on.

47
00:02:44,624 --> 00:02:45,545
These two contracts,

48
00:02:45,624 --> 00:02:46,744
choose for yourselves.

49
00:02:47,945 --> 00:02:49,304
But you can't delay any longer.

50
00:02:49,665 --> 00:02:51,265
A decision must be made now.

51
00:02:52,225 --> 00:02:52,785
Xiaoyu,

52
00:02:53,184 --> 00:02:54,105
hand out the contracts.

53
00:03:05,265 --> 00:03:06,464
Try to lower the prices first.

54
00:03:06,744 --> 00:03:07,985
Get as much as we can.

55
00:03:08,545 --> 00:03:10,545
If not, just play along with her.

56
00:03:10,624 --> 00:03:11,265
Xiaoyu.

57
00:03:12,184 --> 00:03:13,176
(Property Deed Transfer Agreement)
I'll take another one.

58
00:03:13,304 --> 00:03:14,945
- I want to take a gamble.
- If you miss it, it's gone.

59
00:03:17,904 --> 00:03:18,825
Remember to grab a pen.

60
00:03:19,704 --> 00:03:20,665
Once you've decided,

61
00:03:20,864 --> 00:03:21,880
sign it immediately.

62
00:03:22,144 --> 00:03:23,144
Come to me for the check.

63
00:03:24,665 --> 00:03:25,225
Fatty,

64
00:03:25,624 --> 00:03:26,704
you should stop hesitating.

65
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:27,576
Okay?

66
00:03:27,864 --> 00:03:29,744
Sell your shop to me
for an extra 10,000 yuan.

67
00:03:29,848 --> 00:03:30,424
Okay?

68
00:03:31,928 --> 00:03:35,017
♪And the dazed confusion♪

69
00:03:35,985 --> 00:03:36,920
Who said I won't sign?

70
00:03:37,225 --> 00:03:37,744
You just said

71
00:03:37,784 --> 00:03:39,032
- the two of us will definitely do this.
- How much are you giving me?

72
00:03:39,032 --> 00:03:39,785
I'm telling you.

73
00:03:40,024 --> 00:03:41,825
You and you,

74
00:03:43,184 --> 00:03:43,744
today,

75
00:03:44,105 --> 00:03:46,024
really won't be able
to take my plots from me.

76
00:03:46,385 --> 00:03:47,864
The government's decision is bold.

77
00:03:48,024 --> 00:03:50,584
Xuemei's idea today is also a bold move.

78
00:03:50,704 --> 00:03:51,825
You following her,

79
00:03:52,265 --> 00:03:54,024
and me being the first to sign today,

80
00:03:54,184 --> 00:03:55,184
are also bold moves!

81
00:03:55,945 --> 00:03:56,864
You one,

82
00:03:57,105 --> 00:03:57,864
she two,

83
00:03:57,945 --> 00:03:58,785
and me three.

84
00:04:00,624 --> 00:04:01,505
Learned foreign words?

85
00:04:02,825 --> 00:04:03,785
Enough talk. Let's sign.

86
00:04:03,945 --> 00:04:04,985
I'm crazy.

87
00:04:05,065 --> 00:04:05,880
Just for Xuemei.

88
00:04:19,545 --> 00:04:20,585
Leaving right now?

89
00:04:21,545 --> 00:04:23,145
Mr. Zheng said he'd treat you to a meal.

90
00:04:23,665 --> 00:04:26,064
There's a project in Jinhai.
I have to chair a meeting.

91
00:04:26,785 --> 00:04:27,785
Called me several times.

92
00:04:28,905 --> 00:04:30,624
So you won't abandon Yuehai, will you?

93
00:04:30,985 --> 00:04:31,545
Of course not.

94
00:04:31,985 --> 00:04:32,905
For your project here,

95
00:04:33,624 --> 00:04:35,545
I'll remain your chief consultant.

96
00:04:35,864 --> 00:04:37,384
If Mr. Lin has any problems,

97
00:04:37,424 --> 00:04:38,424
contact me anytime.

98
00:04:40,545 --> 00:04:42,665
Then don't you dare
not answer when we call.

99
00:04:46,585 --> 00:04:48,225
How could I dare not answer your call?

100
00:04:48,944 --> 00:04:49,496
To be honest,

101
00:04:49,496 --> 00:04:50,584
when I first came here,

102
00:04:50,584 --> 00:04:51,905
I only came because of you.

103
00:04:52,264 --> 00:04:53,705
But Yuehai's cadres

104
00:04:54,264 --> 00:04:55,105
are truly impressive.

105
00:04:55,504 --> 00:04:56,785
Everyone gets things done.

106
00:04:57,705 --> 00:04:59,905
That Mr. Lin especially opened my eyes.

107
00:05:00,225 --> 00:05:01,864
He might lack theoretical knowledge,

108
00:05:02,105 --> 00:05:03,304
but he's eager to learn.

109
00:05:03,465 --> 00:05:05,624
He read all the books I recommended.

110
00:05:06,025 --> 00:05:08,264
Mr. Lin is a very genuine person.

111
00:05:08,624 --> 00:05:09,465
He's reliable too.

112
00:05:10,545 --> 00:05:11,504
So you can rest easy.

113
00:05:13,905 --> 00:05:14,424
I'm leaving.

114
00:05:15,824 --> 00:05:16,424
Just stay here.

115
00:05:16,504 --> 00:05:17,624
You know I hate goodbyes.

116
00:05:21,384 --> 00:05:21,985
He's really...

117
00:05:22,424 --> 00:05:23,545
Oh, right, one more thing.

118
00:05:24,264 --> 00:05:25,545
Never delay the project.

119
00:05:25,985 --> 00:05:28,145
If a typhoon hits
during the enclosure stage,

120
00:05:28,184 --> 00:05:29,225
it'll be a disaster.

121
00:05:29,545 --> 00:05:30,145
I know.

122
00:05:30,624 --> 00:05:32,264
The weather's more temperamental.

123
00:05:32,424 --> 00:05:33,624
They can turn on you anytime.

124
00:05:36,344 --> 00:05:36,952
Qi...

125
00:05:41,105 --> 00:05:41,824
Thank you.

126
00:05:44,705 --> 00:05:45,424
Good luck.

127
00:05:50,616 --> 00:05:53,208
(Binhai 1st Road)

128
00:05:54,776 --> 00:05:56,472
(No Entry, Huacai Printery)

129
00:05:57,208 --> 00:05:59,576
(Construction Area, No Entry)

130
00:05:59,576 --> 00:06:01,272
(No Entry)

131
00:06:01,272 --> 00:06:03,096
(Chunmei Printery)

132
00:06:03,096 --> 00:06:05,016
(Fatty Printery)

133
00:06:15,744 --> 00:06:16,905
Where is Foreman Song?

134
00:06:17,264 --> 00:06:18,225
Why isn't he here?

135
00:06:18,456 --> 00:06:19,504
(Welcome City Construction Team
to Yuehai)

136
00:06:19,504 --> 00:06:20,384
We don't know either.

137
00:06:20,624 --> 00:06:22,824
Foreman Song might
have been held up by something.

138
00:06:23,465 --> 00:06:24,064
How about...

139
00:06:24,424 --> 00:06:25,744
How about we get started first?

140
00:06:29,705 --> 00:06:30,225
All right.

141
00:06:31,585 --> 00:06:32,184
First,

142
00:06:32,424 --> 00:06:33,705
let's give a round of applause

143
00:06:34,105 --> 00:06:35,905
to welcome the city construction team

144
00:06:36,064 --> 00:06:36,785
to Yuehai.

145
00:06:40,985 --> 00:06:42,025
Starting today,

146
00:06:42,545 --> 00:06:45,665
our land expansion project
officially begins.

147
00:06:46,145 --> 00:06:47,905
Since Foreman Song isn't here,

148
00:06:48,225 --> 00:06:50,504
let's invite our town's
head of construction, Mr. Lin,

149
00:06:50,665 --> 00:06:51,264
to speak.

150
00:06:58,360 --> 00:06:58,905
Well...

151
00:06:59,105 --> 00:06:59,744
It's just...

152
00:07:00,145 --> 00:07:02,585
Foreman Song should
be the one briefing us.

153
00:07:02,785 --> 00:07:04,744
I didn't prepare anything in advance.

154
00:07:05,496 --> 00:07:06,072
Well...

155
00:07:08,024 --> 00:07:08,545
Song...

156
00:07:08,905 --> 00:07:10,585
- Foreman Song is here.
- Foreman Song, you're finally here.

157
00:07:10,785 --> 00:07:12,025
Everyone's waiting for you.

158
00:07:12,785 --> 00:07:13,424
Foreman Song.

159
00:07:13,864 --> 00:07:14,424
Well...

160
00:07:14,785 --> 00:07:15,785
Foreman Song is here,

161
00:07:15,944 --> 00:07:17,304
so let's invite him to speak.

162
00:07:19,608 --> 00:07:26,585
(Welcome City Construction Team
to Yuehai)

163
00:07:26,585 --> 00:07:27,905
Do I still need to make a speech?

164
00:07:28,744 --> 00:07:29,705
Okay, then I'll

165
00:07:30,064 --> 00:07:30,985
say a few words.

166
00:07:33,105 --> 00:07:34,665
Before coming to Yuehai, I heard

167
00:07:35,665 --> 00:07:36,792
that this town is all

168
00:07:37,225 --> 00:07:38,145
about efficiency,

169
00:07:38,824 --> 00:07:39,624
no ostentation,

170
00:07:40,225 --> 00:07:41,465
and no formalism.

171
00:07:43,064 --> 00:07:44,145
But now, it seems

172
00:07:45,424 --> 00:07:46,744
legends are just legends.

173
00:07:50,504 --> 00:07:51,545
I think

174
00:07:52,744 --> 00:07:54,304
today's welcome ceremony

175
00:07:56,424 --> 00:07:57,744
is putting pressure on us.

176
00:07:59,608 --> 00:08:00,264
Of course,

177
00:08:01,944 --> 00:08:03,624
I'm in construction,
not good with words.

178
00:08:04,264 --> 00:08:05,064
But I know

179
00:08:05,504 --> 00:08:07,624
that results aren't achieved by talking,

180
00:08:09,025 --> 00:08:11,665
but by solid work.

181
00:08:15,665 --> 00:08:17,105
Here comes another Lin.

182
00:08:17,785 --> 00:08:19,504
On a project,
people like him are a plus,

183
00:08:19,504 --> 00:08:20,024
right?

184
00:08:20,824 --> 00:08:21,545
I believe

185
00:08:22,025 --> 00:08:23,985
we have the confidence
and the capability

186
00:08:24,905 --> 00:08:26,465
to win this tough battle.

187
00:08:26,985 --> 00:08:27,744
Am I right?

188
00:08:27,864 --> 00:08:28,504
- Yes!
- Yes!

189
00:08:29,624 --> 00:08:30,225
I declare

190
00:08:30,744 --> 00:08:31,705
we officially station

191
00:08:32,105 --> 00:08:32,945
at Binhai 1st Road.

192
00:08:36,920 --> 00:08:38,680
(Welcome City Construction Team
to Yuehai)

193
00:08:38,680 --> 00:08:42,968
(Binhai 1st Road)

194
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:48,632
♪Great causes follow the Party's lead♪

195
00:08:48,824 --> 00:08:52,390
♪Sweat soaks this passionate land♪

196
00:08:53,560 --> 00:08:54,584
(Fatty Printery)

197
00:08:56,472 --> 00:08:59,972
♪Good news flies from every front♪

198
00:09:01,144 --> 00:09:02,456
(Police)

199
00:09:04,152 --> 00:09:07,352
♪The vast land bathes
in the morning glow♪

200
00:09:08,384 --> 00:09:09,105
Take it slow.

201
00:09:09,264 --> 00:09:10,624
Voice down. Everyone's sleeping.

202
00:09:11,704 --> 00:09:14,933
♪The glorious rays
shine on the new society♪

203
00:09:16,185 --> 00:09:17,465
Foreman Song is exhausted.

204
00:09:17,784 --> 00:09:19,144
He fell asleep before finishing.

205
00:09:19,504 --> 00:09:21,904
He hasn't had
a full night's sleep in days,

206
00:09:22,065 --> 00:09:23,345
always staying at the site.

207
00:09:23,504 --> 00:09:24,744
Whenever I go, he's there.

208
00:09:24,920 --> 00:09:25,624
Yes.

209
00:09:26,024 --> 00:09:27,585
And they work through the night,

210
00:09:27,664 --> 00:09:28,384
which is tough.

211
00:09:28,536 --> 00:09:29,065
Yes.

212
00:09:29,305 --> 00:09:30,144
I've calculated

213
00:09:30,825 --> 00:09:32,065
that at the current pace,

214
00:09:33,144 --> 00:09:35,185
we can complete the enclosure two months

215
00:09:35,425 --> 00:09:36,185
ahead of schedule.

216
00:09:38,585 --> 00:09:41,105
This pace was achieved
at the cost of their lives.

217
00:09:41,465 --> 00:09:42,552
We must take care of them.

218
00:09:43,160 --> 00:09:43,704
Yes.

219
00:09:47,664 --> 00:09:48,585
Place the items.

220
00:09:49,185 --> 00:09:49,825
Keep it down.

221
00:09:50,225 --> 00:09:51,425
Don't disturb everyone's rest.

222
00:09:51,608 --> 00:09:52,152
Okay.

223
00:09:52,408 --> 00:09:53,024
Hurry up.

224
00:09:53,024 --> 00:09:53,864
It's so heavy.

225
00:09:54,144 --> 00:09:55,305
Can you get some exercise?

226
00:09:55,504 --> 00:09:56,264
Look at you.

227
00:10:05,185 --> 00:10:05,825
He's awake.

228
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:12,305
Everyone, wake up.

229
00:10:14,504 --> 00:10:15,945
Didn't I tell you

230
00:10:16,024 --> 00:10:17,624
to wake me after eating? You...

231
00:10:18,585 --> 00:10:19,744
- I fell asleep.
- Foreman Song.

232
00:10:19,904 --> 00:10:21,144
- Sorry.
- Get up now.

233
00:10:21,345 --> 00:10:22,225
I was just too tired.

234
00:10:22,264 --> 00:10:23,544
I-I just dozed off for a bit.

235
00:10:24,465 --> 00:10:25,624
Alright, get to work.

236
00:10:25,825 --> 00:10:26,825
Get up.

237
00:10:27,345 --> 00:10:28,225
Get up.

238
00:10:28,225 --> 00:10:28,864
Time to work.

239
00:10:29,240 --> 00:10:29,744
Come on.

240
00:10:29,784 --> 00:10:30,392
Quickly.

241
00:10:30,664 --> 00:10:31,504
Work time.

242
00:10:31,864 --> 00:10:32,585
Look at the time.

243
00:10:33,024 --> 00:10:33,864
Stop sitting around!

244
00:10:33,904 --> 00:10:34,904
It's okay, Foreman Song.

245
00:10:34,904 --> 00:10:36,264
Maybe you should rest more.

246
00:10:36,504 --> 00:10:37,664
We've rested enough.

247
00:10:37,744 --> 00:10:39,185
It's been ten minutes.

248
00:10:39,345 --> 00:10:40,024
Here's the thing.

249
00:10:40,345 --> 00:10:42,144
Since the project
is progressing so smoothly,

250
00:10:42,425 --> 00:10:42,925
why not

251
00:10:42,945 --> 00:10:44,384
give everyone half a day off today?

252
00:10:44,504 --> 00:10:45,264
Let them rest.

253
00:10:45,425 --> 00:10:46,384
What're you saying?

254
00:10:46,744 --> 00:10:47,585
We've eaten.

255
00:10:47,825 --> 00:10:48,504
Look.

256
00:10:48,544 --> 00:10:49,664
The rest... Hurry up!

257
00:10:50,465 --> 00:10:51,544
We've rested, right?

258
00:10:52,065 --> 00:10:52,624
Foreman Song,

259
00:10:52,705 --> 00:10:53,904
we're not pressed for time.

260
00:10:54,425 --> 00:10:56,065
Mr. Zheng said half a day off.

261
00:10:56,105 --> 00:10:57,065
Just take a rest.

262
00:10:57,144 --> 00:10:57,705
Mr. Lin,

263
00:10:58,024 --> 00:10:59,504
Mr. Zheng might not know, but you do.

264
00:10:59,605 --> 00:11:01,024
Our work is like fighting a war.

265
00:11:01,945 --> 00:11:03,465
You haven't rested much up to now.

266
00:11:04,105 --> 00:11:05,024
He didn't rest either.

267
00:11:05,825 --> 00:11:06,325
I'm going.

268
00:11:09,024 --> 00:11:09,585
Alright.

269
00:11:09,904 --> 00:11:11,065
Let's have a brief meeting.

270
00:11:11,144 --> 00:11:11,644
Okay.

271
00:11:12,065 --> 00:11:12,565
Let's go.

272
00:11:12,624 --> 00:11:13,664
You know? All for you.

273
00:11:13,705 --> 00:11:14,384
Thank you.

274
00:11:14,384 --> 00:11:15,185
Come forward!

275
00:11:15,264 --> 00:11:15,764
Come!

276
00:11:15,992 --> 00:11:17,544
Soap, toothbrushes, laundry detergent.

277
00:11:17,664 --> 00:11:19,244
- Come on. There's more here.
- Save me a bag of fruit.

278
00:11:19,425 --> 00:11:20,225
I just need this.

279
00:11:20,305 --> 00:11:22,225
- Too busy to go buy any.
- Soap, toothbrushes, laundry detergent.

280
00:11:22,264 --> 00:11:22,904
What's going on?

281
00:11:23,024 --> 00:11:23,864
Thank you.

282
00:11:24,185 --> 00:11:24,864
Take one each.

283
00:11:27,384 --> 00:11:27,904
Foreman Song,

284
00:11:28,185 --> 00:11:28,904
hello.

285
00:11:29,185 --> 00:11:29,945
I'm Gao Xuemei

286
00:11:29,985 --> 00:11:32,124
from Chunmei Printery Ltd.

287
00:11:32,144 --> 00:11:32,664
Ms. Gao.

288
00:11:32,784 --> 00:11:33,544
Yes. We've seen

289
00:11:33,585 --> 00:11:34,864
you've worked day and night

290
00:11:34,904 --> 00:11:36,600
for this project. It's incredibly tough.

291
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:38,305
- Exactly.
- We didn't know how to express it,

292
00:11:38,624 --> 00:11:39,904
so we prepared some gifts

293
00:11:40,065 --> 00:11:40,904
to reward everyone.

294
00:11:41,065 --> 00:11:42,345
Apples, pears, and oranges.

295
00:11:42,425 --> 00:11:43,384
Lots of fruit.

296
00:11:45,624 --> 00:11:46,185
Put it down.

297
00:11:50,065 --> 00:11:50,985
Put it all down!

298
00:11:51,384 --> 00:11:53,985
- Wait. It's just a small token.
- This is truly from our hearts.

299
00:11:55,784 --> 00:11:56,504
I'm telling you.

300
00:11:57,225 --> 00:11:58,936
I don't care what the rules were

301
00:11:58,936 --> 00:11:59,672
at other sites.

302
00:12:00,384 --> 00:12:01,144
On my site,

303
00:12:01,305 --> 00:12:03,024
you follow my rules.

304
00:12:04,225 --> 00:12:06,585
No taking even a needle
or thread from the people!

305
00:12:09,105 --> 00:12:10,825
- That's a bit exaggerated.
- Foreman Song, yes.

306
00:12:10,985 --> 00:12:11,504
Yes, right.

307
00:12:11,744 --> 00:12:13,465
- It's also from us Yuehai residents.
- It's Yuehai residents'

308
00:12:13,465 --> 00:12:14,520
- We represent the people.
- token of appreciation.

309
00:12:14,585 --> 00:12:15,425
I appreciate it,

310
00:12:16,784 --> 00:12:17,864
but I have my rules.

311
00:12:19,465 --> 00:12:20,664
Just a small token from them.

312
00:12:21,705 --> 00:12:22,664
If you take it,

313
00:12:23,544 --> 00:12:25,624
I'll settle your pay right now today,

314
00:12:25,784 --> 00:12:26,305
and you go.

315
00:12:30,105 --> 00:12:30,985
Understood?

316
00:12:33,705 --> 00:12:34,225
Get to work!

317
00:12:37,305 --> 00:12:37,864
That bad?

318
00:12:37,985 --> 00:12:39,416
Even small amounts wasted add up.

319
00:12:40,264 --> 00:12:40,904
It's weird.

320
00:12:40,985 --> 00:12:42,945
See? What do you mean by "weird"?

321
00:12:43,065 --> 00:12:44,264
Upright and incarruptible.

322
00:12:44,945 --> 00:12:46,504
What "incarruptible"? Incorruptible.

323
00:12:46,544 --> 00:12:47,264
Incorruptible.

324
00:12:47,345 --> 00:12:48,305
That spirit,

325
00:12:48,705 --> 00:12:50,105
though the gift wasn't accepted,

326
00:12:50,345 --> 00:12:51,384
we learned from it, right?

327
00:12:51,465 --> 00:12:51,965
But...

328
00:12:52,024 --> 00:12:52,585
Have we?

329
00:12:52,624 --> 00:12:53,784
Our project is secured.

330
00:12:54,965 --> 00:12:55,864
- Touched me to tears.
- Stop eating.

331
00:12:55,864 --> 00:12:56,825
- All you do is eating all day.
- So touched.

332
00:12:56,856 --> 00:12:57,880
Not everyone's like you.

333
00:13:10,744 --> 00:13:11,425
Mr. Zheng!

334
00:13:12,225 --> 00:13:12,864
Ms. Li!

335
00:13:14,144 --> 00:13:14,705
Mr. Zheng!

336
00:13:14,904 --> 00:13:15,585
Mr. Zheng!

337
00:13:16,105 --> 00:13:16,664
Ms. Li!

338
00:13:17,705 --> 00:13:18,205
What's up?

339
00:13:18,504 --> 00:13:19,105
What happened?

340
00:13:21,144 --> 00:13:22,185
The cement has an issue.

341
00:13:23,744 --> 00:13:24,544
What issues?

342
00:13:25,185 --> 00:13:26,065
Per standards,

343
00:13:26,105 --> 00:13:29,065
concrete piles need high-strength

344
00:13:29,544 --> 00:13:31,864
special cement resistant
to seawater corrosion.

345
00:13:32,345 --> 00:13:34,585
But today at the site, I likely saw them

346
00:13:35,544 --> 00:13:37,024
mixed in low-grade cement.

347
00:13:39,345 --> 00:13:40,624
You saw this yourself?

348
00:13:41,105 --> 00:13:42,784
I missed the mixing process,

349
00:13:43,585 --> 00:13:45,624
but after decades working with cement,

350
00:13:45,864 --> 00:13:47,345
I can tell whether the cement

351
00:13:47,384 --> 00:13:48,664
is special or ordinary by touch.

352
00:13:48,985 --> 00:13:49,664
I'm sure.

353
00:13:50,024 --> 00:13:50,544
Yes.

354
00:13:50,945 --> 00:13:52,744
And they mix cement

355
00:13:52,864 --> 00:13:53,705
every night.

356
00:13:54,225 --> 00:13:55,065
Could they be

357
00:13:55,345 --> 00:13:56,384
avoiding us?

358
00:13:57,384 --> 00:13:58,024
Well then.

359
00:13:58,624 --> 00:14:00,744
Get Foreman Song over here now.

360
00:14:00,864 --> 00:14:01,705
Let's clear this up.

361
00:14:02,305 --> 00:14:03,225
That won't work.

362
00:14:03,664 --> 00:14:04,264
Why not?

363
00:14:04,585 --> 00:14:07,065
You think Foreman Song's involved?

364
00:14:09,825 --> 00:14:10,705
Very possible.

365
00:14:11,264 --> 00:14:12,784
Given how he operates,

366
00:14:13,105 --> 00:14:14,904
he must've known his people

367
00:14:14,945 --> 00:14:16,105
are doing this.

368
00:14:16,825 --> 00:14:18,040
And during cement mixing,

369
00:14:18,040 --> 00:14:19,465
he was always at the site.

370
00:14:19,624 --> 00:14:20,504
Then why wait?

371
00:14:20,904 --> 00:14:21,864
Let's go now...

372
00:14:21,864 --> 00:14:23,465
We need concrete proof first.

373
00:14:23,744 --> 00:14:25,105
We can't falsely accuse anyone.

374
00:14:25,305 --> 00:14:26,744
But we also can't tip them off.

375
00:14:27,024 --> 00:14:28,585
But Lin already identified it.

376
00:14:28,825 --> 00:14:30,425
Let's just test it directly.

377
00:14:30,705 --> 00:14:31,305
Mr. Zheng,

378
00:14:31,705 --> 00:14:33,705
my master and I are most concerned

379
00:14:33,904 --> 00:14:35,264
about whether low-grade cement

380
00:14:35,544 --> 00:14:37,425
was mixed into the submerged
concrete piles.

381
00:14:37,465 --> 00:14:38,024
Exactly!

382
00:14:38,345 --> 00:14:39,784
I'll call the county immediately

383
00:14:40,105 --> 00:14:42,624
to arrange underwater inspectors

384
00:14:43,024 --> 00:14:44,105
with proper equipment.

385
00:14:44,305 --> 00:14:45,024
Wait. Ms. Li.

386
00:14:45,065 --> 00:14:47,264
That bureaucratic process
will take forever!

387
00:14:47,305 --> 00:14:47,904
Right now,

388
00:14:48,705 --> 00:14:50,225
we can't afford delays.

389
00:14:50,345 --> 00:14:51,305
You know. Every day,

390
00:14:51,544 --> 00:14:52,568
they mix low-grade cement

391
00:14:52,568 --> 00:14:53,945
into the concrete piles.

392
00:14:54,744 --> 00:14:55,244
Well,

393
00:14:55,425 --> 00:14:55,925
I'll

394
00:14:56,024 --> 00:14:57,504
dive down for a sample myself.

395
00:14:57,544 --> 00:14:58,185
It's faster.

396
00:14:58,305 --> 00:14:59,185
No way!

397
00:14:59,624 --> 00:15:00,305
Yeah, Master.

398
00:15:00,384 --> 00:15:02,328
We agreed, no reckless moves!

399
00:15:02,328 --> 00:15:04,056
Leave it to the professionals.

400
00:15:04,120 --> 00:15:06,624
I was in the navy.
Diving's my expertise.

401
00:15:06,664 --> 00:15:07,705
I'll be okay, Mr. Zheng.

402
00:15:08,264 --> 00:15:08,764
Okay.

403
00:15:08,945 --> 00:15:09,985
Even if you can dive,

404
00:15:10,664 --> 00:15:12,185
sampling isn't fetching objects.

405
00:15:12,504 --> 00:15:13,305
H-How to fetch it?

406
00:15:13,504 --> 00:15:14,144
Tell me!

407
00:15:14,465 --> 00:15:15,065
Exactly.

408
00:15:15,305 --> 00:15:15,864
Mr. Lin,

409
00:15:16,065 --> 00:15:17,185
I'm no engineer,

410
00:15:17,544 --> 00:15:18,585
but I know

411
00:15:18,585 --> 00:15:20,185
y-you can't exert force underwater.

412
00:15:20,425 --> 00:15:21,305
It's totally different

413
00:15:21,345 --> 00:15:23,185
from chipping cement on land.

414
00:15:23,744 --> 00:15:25,264
And you haven't dived in years.

415
00:15:25,544 --> 00:15:26,705
It's too risky.

416
00:15:29,144 --> 00:15:29,664
Wait, Ms. Li.

417
00:15:29,664 --> 00:15:31,585
Y-You really
don't understand engineering.

418
00:15:31,624 --> 00:15:33,185
This is a race against time.

419
00:15:33,345 --> 00:15:35,784
And it was me who failed in supervision.

420
00:15:35,945 --> 00:15:37,305
So now, I must...

421
00:15:37,305 --> 00:15:38,904
Alright, just spare me the chatter.

422
00:15:39,904 --> 00:15:40,728
No means no.

423
00:15:40,945 --> 00:15:42,024
Just stay here.

424
00:15:42,345 --> 00:15:43,105
Don't go anywhere!

425
00:15:43,425 --> 00:15:43,945
Got it?

426
00:15:45,305 --> 00:15:45,904
Mr. Lin,

427
00:15:46,144 --> 00:15:47,945
you must listen to Mr. Zheng this time.

428
00:15:48,465 --> 00:15:49,985
We'll keep an eye out these days

429
00:15:50,664 --> 00:15:52,425
and see if they have
any unusual behavior.

430
00:15:53,425 --> 00:15:54,105
Okay.

431
00:16:46,744 --> 00:16:47,384
What?

432
00:16:48,225 --> 00:16:50,705
The sampling equipment can
only be sent here three days later?

433
00:16:51,624 --> 00:16:53,664
Could you please coordinate again?

434
00:16:54,185 --> 00:16:55,185
This test

435
00:16:55,384 --> 00:16:57,205
is really urgent for us.

436
00:16:57,205 --> 00:16:58,425
- Ms. Li.
- Thank you.

437
00:16:58,744 --> 00:16:59,544
Something happened.

438
00:16:59,585 --> 00:17:00,425
- Alright, goodbye.
- Something happened.

439
00:17:00,985 --> 00:17:01,705
What's wrong, Yu?

440
00:17:01,945 --> 00:17:03,065
Something came up on site.

441
00:17:03,105 --> 00:17:04,064
I wanted to find Master.

442
00:17:04,304 --> 00:17:05,905
But I couldn't find him anywhere.

443
00:17:06,264 --> 00:17:07,385
When I just got back,

444
00:17:07,385 --> 00:17:08,465
Mr. Hailuo told me

445
00:17:08,905 --> 00:17:11,544
that he saw my master
carrying an oxygen tank out today.

446
00:17:12,465 --> 00:17:12,985
Oh, no.

447
00:17:13,625 --> 00:17:14,304
Wouldn't Lin dive

448
00:17:14,784 --> 00:17:16,385
into the sea
to sample himself, would he?

449
00:17:19,104 --> 00:17:20,344
Let's go to the beach.

450
00:17:21,344 --> 00:17:21,985
To the beach.

451
00:17:38,024 --> 00:17:38,665
Lin!

452
00:17:39,185 --> 00:17:40,064
Master!

453
00:17:40,064 --> 00:17:40,905
Mr. Lin!

454
00:17:41,425 --> 00:17:42,104
Lin!

455
00:17:42,304 --> 00:17:43,145
Master!

456
00:17:44,784 --> 00:17:45,544
Lin!

457
00:17:45,816 --> 00:17:46,744
Mr. Lin!

458
00:17:47,104 --> 00:17:47,824
Lin!

459
00:17:47,824 --> 00:17:49,185
- Mr. Lin!
- Master!

460
00:17:51,304 --> 00:17:51,985
Lin!

461
00:17:52,625 --> 00:17:53,784
Master!

462
00:17:57,784 --> 00:17:58,392
Mr. Lin!

463
00:17:58,392 --> 00:17:58,945
There he is.

464
00:18:01,304 --> 00:18:01,865
Master!

465
00:18:02,425 --> 00:18:03,665
Lin Dongfu, are you crazy?

466
00:18:03,865 --> 00:18:04,905
You sampled in the water?

467
00:18:05,225 --> 00:18:06,232
What are you doing?

468
00:18:06,232 --> 00:18:07,385
You scared us to death.

469
00:18:08,145 --> 00:18:08,744
Are you okay?

470
00:18:08,784 --> 00:18:09,284
Well...

471
00:18:13,264 --> 00:18:13,865
Mr. Zheng.

472
00:18:14,905 --> 00:18:15,425
Ms. Li.

473
00:18:16,385 --> 00:18:17,264
I'm really fine.

474
00:18:18,225 --> 00:18:18,945
That sample

475
00:18:19,304 --> 00:18:21,185
h-has been retrieved.

476
00:18:23,625 --> 00:18:24,905
Don't think you've made it

477
00:18:25,104 --> 00:18:26,024
and I won't scold you.

478
00:18:26,824 --> 00:18:28,304
You were too impulsive, you know?

479
00:18:28,584 --> 00:18:29,496
It's nothing.

480
00:18:30,225 --> 00:18:31,304
Back when I was in the Navy

481
00:18:33,625 --> 00:18:34,504
in a diving match,

482
00:18:35,104 --> 00:18:36,145
I got second place.

483
00:18:36,544 --> 00:18:37,465
That was back then.

484
00:18:37,945 --> 00:18:38,744
How old were you?

485
00:18:38,865 --> 00:18:39,665
How old are you now?

486
00:18:40,064 --> 00:18:40,744
Mr. Lin,

487
00:18:41,145 --> 00:18:42,024
you've worked hard.

488
00:18:42,185 --> 00:18:43,104
Go back and rest well.

489
00:18:43,304 --> 00:18:43,824
But

490
00:18:44,104 --> 00:18:46,465
you still need to submit
a review tomorrow,

491
00:18:46,824 --> 00:18:48,952
reflecting on your disorganized behavior

492
00:18:48,952 --> 00:18:50,024
deeply.

493
00:18:50,225 --> 00:18:50,865
Do you hear me?

494
00:18:51,104 --> 00:18:51,744
Okay.

495
00:18:52,145 --> 00:18:53,465
I-I will do what Ms. Li said.

496
00:18:54,625 --> 00:18:55,125
By the way,

497
00:18:55,665 --> 00:18:57,304
I just rode my bike over here.

498
00:18:57,665 --> 00:18:58,744
When passing Yuehai Street,

499
00:18:59,344 --> 00:19:00,705
I noticed there were several

500
00:19:01,344 --> 00:19:03,504
very clear truck tire marks.

501
00:19:04,584 --> 00:19:05,705
Yuehai Street is narrow,

502
00:19:06,104 --> 00:19:07,960
and trucks normally wouldn't go there.

503
00:19:08,104 --> 00:19:08,824
I'm wondering

504
00:19:09,705 --> 00:19:11,128
that would the low-grade cement

505
00:19:11,945 --> 00:19:13,064
be transported

506
00:19:13,865 --> 00:19:14,705
and brought in

507
00:19:16,225 --> 00:19:17,064
via Yuehai Street.

508
00:19:18,784 --> 00:19:20,145
We need to find evidence soon.

509
00:19:24,385 --> 00:19:25,304
We've got the sample.

510
00:19:25,705 --> 00:19:27,985
I'll personally go
to the city's testing center.

511
00:19:33,544 --> 00:19:35,000
It will take at least five days.

512
00:19:35,185 --> 00:19:36,184
I think a round trip

513
00:19:36,705 --> 00:19:37,784
might cost over five days.

514
00:19:38,064 --> 00:19:38,905
I know.

515
00:19:38,945 --> 00:19:39,865
Alright, no problem.

516
00:19:40,104 --> 00:19:41,496
Now, I'm more anxious than you.

517
00:19:43,905 --> 00:19:44,865
So what should we do?

518
00:19:45,264 --> 00:19:45,824
Go back?

519
00:19:46,544 --> 00:19:47,425
That's not a problem.

520
00:19:49,564 --> 00:19:50,625
- Okay.
- Excuse me.

521
00:19:50,776 --> 00:19:51,985
- Thanks.
- But we need to make time...

522
00:19:56,905 --> 00:19:57,744
From Yuehai, right?

523
00:19:57,784 --> 00:19:58,304
Yes.

524
00:19:58,584 --> 00:20:00,145
(Window 4)
Our test results aren't ready yet?

525
00:20:00,544 --> 00:20:01,865
Sir, here's the situation.

526
00:20:02,185 --> 00:20:03,064
Don't rush just yet.

527
00:20:03,304 --> 00:20:04,625
(Window 4)
Your county office already called us.

528
00:20:04,824 --> 00:20:05,905
It should be ready today.

529
00:20:06,104 --> 00:20:07,128
Tomorrow at the latest.

530
00:20:07,225 --> 00:20:08,304
We've already expedited it.

531
00:20:08,324 --> 00:20:09,225
- Just wait a bit longer.
- Okay.

532
00:20:09,225 --> 00:20:09,784
It's just...

533
00:20:09,945 --> 00:20:10,445
Sir,

534
00:20:10,584 --> 00:20:12,088
you know, this test result

535
00:20:12,088 --> 00:20:13,665
is critically important for us.

536
00:20:13,865 --> 00:20:15,945
It concerns a major project in Yuehai.

537
00:20:16,584 --> 00:20:18,324
So could you please help push it along?

538
00:20:18,405 --> 00:20:18,905
(Window 4)
Alright.

539
00:20:18,905 --> 00:20:19,405
Thank you.

540
00:20:19,784 --> 00:20:20,385
Okay.

541
00:20:32,625 --> 00:20:33,385
Mr. Lin.

542
00:20:35,304 --> 00:20:36,985
Mr. Lin, wake up.

543
00:20:37,385 --> 00:20:38,304
Time for lunch.

544
00:20:39,905 --> 00:20:40,744
Mr. Lin.

545
00:20:44,264 --> 00:20:44,865
Lin.

546
00:20:45,824 --> 00:20:46,425
Lin.

547
00:20:47,264 --> 00:20:47,945
Lin!

548
00:20:59,096 --> 00:21:01,503
♪You came quietly♪

549
00:21:03,384 --> 00:21:05,934
♪And left quietly♪

550
00:21:07,979 --> 00:21:09,912
♪Perhaps one day♪

551
00:21:10,264 --> 00:21:12,060
♪It won't really matter♪

552
00:21:12,440 --> 00:21:15,104
♪Who will still remember♪

553
00:21:16,271 --> 00:21:19,123
♪You and me♪

554
00:21:23,128 --> 00:21:24,760
Lin Tofu, are you a ghost?

555
00:21:24,760 --> 00:21:25,976
Where'd you pop out from?

556
00:21:26,712 --> 00:21:27,896
I got here yesterday.

557
00:21:29,465 --> 00:21:30,145
Hold steady.

558
00:21:30,145 --> 00:21:30,784
Got it.

559
00:21:32,024 --> 00:21:34,465
(Following the County's
Party Committee evaluation,)

560
00:21:34,648 --> 00:21:35,320
(Lin Dongfu)

561
00:21:35,625 --> 00:21:37,304
(Yuehai Town Master Plan)
(is appointed deputy mayor of Yuehai,)

562
00:21:37,744 --> 00:21:39,288
(overseeing relocation, resettlement,)

563
00:21:39,288 --> 00:21:40,248
(and city construction.)

564
00:21:40,344 --> 00:21:40,985
(Yes.)

565
00:21:42,024 --> 00:21:42,625
Lin.

566
00:21:42,905 --> 00:21:43,625
Here!

567
00:21:43,736 --> 00:21:45,584
You're Yuehai's engine.

568
00:21:46,225 --> 00:21:48,425
Without you, Yuehai would stop running.

569
00:21:51,104 --> 00:21:52,024
Master!

570
00:21:52,024 --> 00:21:52,905
Mr. Lin!

571
00:21:53,824 --> 00:21:54,625
Master!

572
00:21:54,680 --> 00:21:57,656
♪Your shadow in the sunset♪

573
00:21:58,904 --> 00:22:00,696
♪Some are waiting♪

574
00:22:01,824 --> 00:22:02,504
I...

575
00:22:02,985 --> 00:22:03,824
I'm not that...

576
00:22:04,504 --> 00:22:06,024
That good.

577
00:22:07,704 --> 00:22:12,156
♪Thinking of your smile, yet I cried♪

578
00:22:12,945 --> 00:22:14,024
(A beauty I beheld,)

579
00:22:15,304 --> 00:22:16,024
(unforgettable.)

580
00:22:16,792 --> 00:22:18,744
(Even though I've crossed bridges
in many places)

581
00:22:19,185 --> 00:22:20,625
(and seen clouds in many places,)

582
00:22:21,905 --> 00:22:24,665
only your eyes hold skies so clear.

583
00:22:34,425 --> 00:22:35,104
(Master!)

584
00:22:35,865 --> 00:22:36,865
Master, don't scare me!

585
00:22:36,865 --> 00:22:37,784
- Master!
- Mr. Lin!

586
00:22:39,185 --> 00:22:40,248
Master!

587
00:22:42,296 --> 00:22:44,632
Master, get up!

588
00:22:45,803 --> 00:22:47,723
♪It won't really matter♪

589
00:22:48,026 --> 00:22:50,552
♪Who will still remember♪

590
00:22:52,346 --> 00:22:54,296
♪You are a beam of light♪

591
00:22:54,520 --> 00:22:56,581
♪In dazzling years♪

592
00:22:56,920 --> 00:23:00,184
♪Shining on me alone in the dark♪

593
00:23:01,336 --> 00:23:03,320
♪You are a boat♪

594
00:23:03,320 --> 00:23:05,589
♪Carrying our dreams♪

595
00:23:05,848 --> 00:23:08,888
♪Braving the wind and waves
towards the light♪

596
00:23:09,954 --> 00:23:11,960
♪Some are happy♪

597
00:23:11,960 --> 00:23:14,168
♪Leaning on and embracing each other♪

598
00:23:14,392 --> 00:23:18,447
♪Sharing the warmth of their love♪

599
00:23:18,894 --> 00:23:20,984
♪Some are recounting♪

600
00:23:21,368 --> 00:23:23,402
♪Stories of the past♪

601
00:23:23,573 --> 00:23:26,584
♪Your shadow in the sunset♪

602
00:23:27,705 --> 00:23:29,663
♪Some are waiting♪

603
00:23:29,663 --> 00:23:31,800
♪For passengers in life♪

604
00:23:32,241 --> 00:23:36,019
♪Someone is singing that song♪

605
00:23:36,625 --> 00:23:37,465
Hello? Ms. Li,

606
00:23:38,185 --> 00:23:39,504
test results still aren't ready.

607
00:23:40,344 --> 00:23:41,425
Probably tomorrow.

608
00:23:44,945 --> 00:23:45,625
Understood.

609
00:23:51,865 --> 00:23:52,465
Ms. Li?

610
00:23:54,905 --> 00:23:55,824
Are you crying?

611
00:23:56,584 --> 00:23:57,344
Mr. Zheng,

612
00:23:59,824 --> 00:24:01,385
prepare yourself mentally.

613
00:24:02,744 --> 00:24:03,244
What?

614
00:24:03,945 --> 00:24:05,425
P-Prepare for what?

615
00:24:06,104 --> 00:24:07,064
What's happened?

616
00:24:09,504 --> 00:24:10,264
Lin...

617
00:24:12,705 --> 00:24:13,425
Lin...

618
00:24:14,104 --> 00:24:14,865
He's gone.

619
00:24:17,304 --> 00:24:18,064
He's gone?

620
00:24:18,784 --> 00:24:19,665
Where'd he go?

621
00:24:22,040 --> 00:24:22,725
He...

622
00:24:23,865 --> 00:24:25,665
Slept and never woke up.

623
00:24:28,304 --> 00:24:29,064
The doctor said,

624
00:24:29,385 --> 00:24:31,625
he collected samples underwater

625
00:24:32,905 --> 00:24:34,744
and stayed down too long.

626
00:24:36,024 --> 00:24:36,665
His lungs...

627
00:25:21,080 --> 00:25:21,752
Next.

628
00:25:28,865 --> 00:25:29,504
Sir.

629
00:25:31,185 --> 00:25:32,120
Sir,

630
00:25:32,425 --> 00:25:33,385
please wait.

631
00:25:35,625 --> 00:25:36,465
I'm begging you.

632
00:25:38,744 --> 00:25:40,425
Help me hurry it along.

633
00:25:41,824 --> 00:25:42,985
One of our colleagues

634
00:25:44,665 --> 00:25:45,504
sacrificed his life.

635
00:26:04,888 --> 00:26:06,264
I still can't understand.

636
00:26:07,104 --> 00:26:08,344
Mr. Lin was perfectly healthy.

637
00:26:09,385 --> 00:26:10,544
How could he just pass away?

638
00:26:13,104 --> 00:26:13,985
Director Jiang said

639
00:26:15,544 --> 00:26:16,905
it's diver's sickness.

640
00:26:17,665 --> 00:26:19,064
What? What sickness?

641
00:26:21,064 --> 00:26:23,064
Staying deep underwater too long,

642
00:26:24,145 --> 00:26:25,744
and surfacing too quickly.

643
00:26:26,344 --> 00:26:28,465
Gases didn't have time
to leave his body.

644
00:26:29,225 --> 00:26:29,744
So...

645
00:26:35,905 --> 00:26:36,945
I still can't understand.

646
00:27:23,185 --> 00:27:24,856
Do you think Lin Tofu

647
00:27:25,584 --> 00:27:27,665
is playing a joke on us?

648
00:27:36,584 --> 00:27:37,084
Give me.

649
00:28:01,945 --> 00:28:02,445
Hello?

650
00:28:03,584 --> 00:28:04,185
Mr. Zheng.

651
00:28:04,625 --> 00:28:05,225
Ms. Li,

652
00:28:06,185 --> 00:28:07,425
the test results are in.

653
00:28:08,264 --> 00:28:10,064
It confirms the concrete poured in

654
00:28:10,784 --> 00:28:13,024
contained 28% of low-grade cement.

655
00:28:21,465 --> 00:28:22,296
Tan!

656
00:28:37,145 --> 00:28:37,784
Mr. Tian,

657
00:28:38,865 --> 00:28:39,945
Mr. Zheng just called

658
00:28:40,264 --> 00:28:41,784
for what we discussed the other day.

659
00:28:42,225 --> 00:28:43,064
It's confirmed.

660
00:28:43,504 --> 00:28:44,304
We'll act now.

661
00:28:45,104 --> 00:28:46,064
Search the entire town.

662
00:28:46,665 --> 00:28:48,344
Your people can assist too.

663
00:28:48,544 --> 00:28:49,044
Okay.

664
00:28:50,784 --> 00:28:51,425
Tan,

665
00:28:52,625 --> 00:28:54,185
lead the city inspectors

666
00:28:54,744 --> 00:28:55,705
and assist Mr. Tian.

667
00:28:55,905 --> 00:28:56,405
Okay.

668
00:28:56,665 --> 00:28:58,744
Let's split up and cover two fronts.

669
00:28:59,504 --> 00:29:01,145
Ms. Li, wait for our update.

670
00:29:01,344 --> 00:29:01,844
Okay.

671
00:29:09,945 --> 00:29:10,544
Ms. Li.

672
00:29:11,344 --> 00:29:11,945
Ms. Li,

673
00:29:12,385 --> 00:29:14,232
all the high-grade cement
at the site is gone.

674
00:29:14,465 --> 00:29:15,185
Gone?

675
00:29:15,385 --> 00:29:15,885
Yes.

676
00:29:16,185 --> 00:29:17,304
I think someone moved it.

677
00:29:18,385 --> 00:29:19,784
We must notify Mr. Tian quickly

678
00:29:20,104 --> 00:29:21,304
to seal off all roads out.

679
00:29:21,504 --> 00:29:23,584
But Mr. Tian and all the city inspectors

680
00:29:23,744 --> 00:29:25,304
are searching for Foreman Song now.

681
00:29:25,625 --> 00:29:26,865
Besides, with so many roads,

682
00:29:27,064 --> 00:29:28,185
which one to block first?

683
00:29:33,225 --> 00:29:35,344
I'm wondering
that would the low-grade cement

684
00:29:36,225 --> 00:29:37,225
be transported

685
00:29:38,104 --> 00:29:38,905
and brought in

686
00:29:40,465 --> 00:29:41,368
via Yuehai Street.

687
00:29:43,504 --> 00:29:44,945
Yu, come with me.

688
00:29:47,024 --> 00:29:47,832
Where are we going?

689
00:29:49,104 --> 00:29:50,024
Yuehai Street.

690
00:31:19,385 --> 00:31:19,905
Hold on.

691
00:31:20,465 --> 00:31:21,064
Okay.

692
00:31:27,225 --> 00:31:28,185
Be careful, Ms. Li.

693
00:32:08,425 --> 00:32:08,925
What?

694
00:32:09,145 --> 00:32:10,008
Looking for trouble?

695
00:32:10,784 --> 00:32:12,145
What are you hauling?

696
00:32:12,584 --> 00:32:13,185
I'll check.

697
00:32:13,225 --> 00:32:14,504
Who are you? What's it to you?

698
00:32:14,544 --> 00:32:15,665
Can you just talk properly?

699
00:32:16,225 --> 00:32:17,665
This is our mayor, Li Qiuping.

700
00:32:18,185 --> 00:32:18,865
Mayor?

701
00:32:19,425 --> 00:32:20,104
Never seen her.

702
00:32:20,504 --> 00:32:22,104
Is that cement you're hauling?

703
00:32:23,544 --> 00:32:24,264
What cement?

704
00:32:25,584 --> 00:32:26,304
I'm inspecting it.

705
00:32:35,809 --> 00:32:37,720
(Sulfate-resistant cement)

706
00:32:43,544 --> 00:32:45,720
(Sulfate-resistant cement)

707
00:32:47,584 --> 00:32:48,472
We are right.

708
00:33:07,104 --> 00:33:07,705
Li Qiuping!

709
00:33:08,485 --> 00:33:10,104
Tell me, what were you thinking?

710
00:33:10,625 --> 00:33:11,544
Dared stop the truck?

711
00:33:12,064 --> 00:33:13,048
Are you courting death?

712
00:33:13,225 --> 00:33:13,985
I didn't want to.

713
00:33:14,024 --> 00:33:15,264
But they wouldn't stop!

714
00:33:15,425 --> 00:33:16,920
We couldn't stand by and watch them

715
00:33:16,920 --> 00:33:18,185
leave with our cement, right?

716
00:33:18,425 --> 00:33:19,145
Okay, tell me.

717
00:33:19,625 --> 00:33:21,185
Even if you stopped them, failed,

718
00:33:21,544 --> 00:33:22,232
and they left,

719
00:33:22,385 --> 00:33:23,256
where could they go?

720
00:33:23,425 --> 00:33:24,344
The end of the earth?

721
00:33:24,625 --> 00:33:26,744
If we didn't stop them,
it would be too late.

722
00:33:26,865 --> 00:33:27,544
Too late?

723
00:33:28,024 --> 00:33:29,385
So you have to risk your life?

724
00:33:29,665 --> 00:33:30,584
Every one of you wants

725
00:33:30,824 --> 00:33:31,705
to play the hero.

726
00:33:31,945 --> 00:33:33,945
If they made their mind
and ran you over,

727
00:33:34,145 --> 00:33:34,665
what then?

728
00:33:34,865 --> 00:33:35,625
What should I do?

729
00:33:35,945 --> 00:33:37,385
What should Yuehai do?

730
00:33:37,584 --> 00:33:38,945
I understand everything you said.

731
00:33:40,024 --> 00:33:42,104
But the riskier it is,
the more we need to do it.

732
00:33:42,504 --> 00:33:43,584
We can't just watch them

733
00:33:43,905 --> 00:33:45,145
take our cement away!

734
00:33:45,225 --> 00:33:47,145
Otherwise, Lin's sacrifice
would be for nothing.

735
00:34:01,905 --> 00:34:03,352
Mr. Zheng, Ms. Li.

736
00:34:03,865 --> 00:34:04,945
I have something to report.

737
00:34:05,304 --> 00:34:06,104
Sorry to interrupt.

738
00:34:10,624 --> 00:34:11,704
- Tan.
- It's okay.

739
00:34:12,305 --> 00:34:13,064
Sorry.

740
00:34:22,745 --> 00:34:24,224
We caught him.

741
00:34:24,425 --> 00:34:25,544
To the police station.

742
00:34:25,945 --> 00:34:27,465
Mr. Zheng, take it easy.

743
00:34:29,385 --> 00:34:30,785
L-Let me explain.

744
00:34:31,865 --> 00:34:33,305
We caught him first.

745
00:34:34,224 --> 00:34:35,144
He's brought here.

746
00:34:35,465 --> 00:34:36,064
Tan.

747
00:34:36,745 --> 00:34:37,345
Don't worry.

748
00:34:37,905 --> 00:34:38,945
I've already informed

749
00:34:39,465 --> 00:34:40,224
Mr. Tian.

750
00:34:41,104 --> 00:34:42,385
But to be honest,

751
00:34:43,035 --> 00:34:43,384
I don't

752
00:34:44,224 --> 00:34:45,865
want to hand this beast

753
00:34:46,905 --> 00:34:47,945
over.

754
00:34:49,104 --> 00:34:50,144
I really don't.

755
00:35:10,945 --> 00:35:11,745
You two, step out.

756
00:35:31,664 --> 00:35:32,345
Out of cigarette.

757
00:35:36,184 --> 00:35:37,345
Can you grab me a pack?

758
00:35:48,704 --> 00:35:50,184
You're not the police.

759
00:35:51,024 --> 00:35:52,664
What right do you have to arrest me?

760
00:35:53,745 --> 00:35:54,425
Don't worry.

761
00:35:55,144 --> 00:35:56,224
They will be here soon.

762
00:35:58,985 --> 00:36:00,568
Why did you try to ruin us?

763
00:36:01,704 --> 00:36:03,385
What grudge do you have against us?

764
00:36:11,704 --> 00:36:13,224
Have nothing to lose, huh?

765
00:36:13,465 --> 00:36:15,144
Should I show you the test report?

766
00:36:22,024 --> 00:36:22,825
I know.

767
00:36:24,265 --> 00:36:25,656
You must have tested it.

768
00:36:25,985 --> 00:36:26,785
How could you...

769
00:36:27,104 --> 00:36:29,945
How could you trust that data?

770
00:36:32,224 --> 00:36:35,024
I've been in construction for years.
I know it all too well.

771
00:36:35,465 --> 00:36:36,825
Nothing will happen.

772
00:36:37,825 --> 00:36:38,905
And I guarantee you.

773
00:36:39,104 --> 00:36:41,144
Nothing will happen
for eight, even ten years.

774
00:36:41,345 --> 00:36:42,905
Nothing will happen for ten years.

775
00:36:43,104 --> 00:36:43,704
And after that?

776
00:36:44,144 --> 00:36:45,785
After soaking for eight or ten years,

777
00:36:46,144 --> 00:36:47,024
if something happens,

778
00:36:47,104 --> 00:36:49,184
how can you prove
it was my cement's problem?

779
00:36:54,425 --> 00:36:55,865
N-Now that things have come to this,

780
00:36:58,825 --> 00:36:59,745
it is what it is.

781
00:37:01,785 --> 00:37:04,624
You can't possibly
tear it down and rebuild it.

782
00:37:06,985 --> 00:37:07,905
How about this?

783
00:37:16,865 --> 00:37:18,905
Turn a blind eye.

784
00:37:20,204 --> 00:37:21,945
Just pretend it never happened.

785
00:37:25,584 --> 00:37:27,265
Pretend it never happened?

786
00:37:28,425 --> 00:37:30,184
Lin passed away

787
00:37:31,905 --> 00:37:33,664
diving to get samples.

788
00:37:33,785 --> 00:37:35,624
How dare you even mention Lin?

789
00:37:36,265 --> 00:37:37,985
What a good man he was!

790
00:37:40,104 --> 00:37:41,945
It was you who sent him down there.

791
00:37:42,425 --> 00:37:45,465
If you'd told me,
would this have happened?

792
00:37:45,985 --> 00:37:46,624
Lin...

793
00:37:46,865 --> 00:37:48,544
Do you have any conscience saying that?

794
00:37:53,144 --> 00:37:54,024
How about this?

795
00:38:00,064 --> 00:38:02,785
I'll give you half
of what I made selling the cement.

796
00:38:03,224 --> 00:38:03,985
Each of you

797
00:38:04,465 --> 00:38:06,865
could get a good chunk.

798
00:38:07,425 --> 00:38:08,664
I saw how you work every day,

799
00:38:08,704 --> 00:38:09,825
braving wind and rain.

800
00:38:09,865 --> 00:38:12,024
I've seen it. It's too hard.

801
00:38:12,024 --> 00:38:12,905
What are you after?

802
00:38:14,504 --> 00:38:15,544
You're just after

803
00:38:16,104 --> 00:38:17,704
that intangible, untouchable reputation?

804
00:38:18,385 --> 00:38:20,024
How stupid is that?

805
00:38:20,265 --> 00:38:21,912
I'll kill you!

806
00:38:21,912 --> 00:38:22,664
Mr. Zheng!

807
00:38:25,024 --> 00:38:25,524
Hit!

808
00:38:25,524 --> 00:38:27,480
- Murder! Murder!
- Don't hit him!

809
00:38:27,480 --> 00:38:28,536
- Murder!
- Nobody move!

810
00:38:29,400 --> 00:38:30,425
Don't do it, Mr. Zheng.

811
00:38:42,504 --> 00:38:43,624
- They're out!
- Coming!

812
00:38:43,624 --> 00:38:44,265
They're out!

813
00:38:44,265 --> 00:38:44,785
They're out!

814
00:38:45,425 --> 00:38:45,925
Calm down!

815
00:38:46,745 --> 00:38:47,624
Calm down!

816
00:38:47,704 --> 00:38:49,064
You took our hard-earned money!

817
00:38:49,305 --> 00:38:50,544
Don't hit him!

818
00:38:50,724 --> 00:38:51,640
- Calm down!
- Hit him!

819
00:38:52,504 --> 00:38:54,465
Playing tricks with our sweat and blood!

820
00:38:56,104 --> 00:38:57,144
Calm down!

821
00:40:17,144 --> 00:40:21,184
♪My heart is clear to see♪

822
00:40:21,624 --> 00:40:25,584
♪Longing for a true love♪

823
00:40:26,305 --> 00:40:29,785
♪My heart was once broken by love♪

824
00:40:29,985 --> 00:40:35,024
♪Why do sweet dreams end so easily♪

825
00:40:35,465 --> 00:40:38,785
♪You have gentle eyes♪

826
00:40:44,985 --> 00:40:46,664
♪If you're willing♪

827
00:40:47,305 --> 00:40:48,945
♪Please let me near♪

828
00:40:53,865 --> 00:40:58,072
♪Stars shine bright, breeze is light♪

829
00:40:58,865 --> 00:41:02,825
♪I'm a lonely girl♪

830
00:41:03,465 --> 00:41:05,184
♪Bidding farewell to old love♪

831
00:41:05,785 --> 00:41:07,465
♪Smoothing over my wounds♪

832
00:41:07,825 --> 00:41:11,832
♪No more crying until dawn♪

833
00:41:12,144 --> 00:41:16,472
♪Your heart is clear to see♪

834
00:41:17,024 --> 00:41:20,888
♪Longing for a true love♪

835
00:41:21,544 --> 00:41:25,184
♪My heart was once broken by love♪

836
00:41:25,425 --> 00:41:32,385
♪Why do sweet dreams end so easily♪

837
00:41:38,624 --> 00:41:40,504
Yan, what are you doing?

838
00:41:40,825 --> 00:41:41,905
Why aren't the lights on?

839
00:41:42,345 --> 00:41:43,224
Yeah, Yan.

840
00:41:43,385 --> 00:41:44,664
Why are you here so early today?

841
00:41:45,825 --> 00:41:46,425
It's nothing.

842
00:41:47,425 --> 00:41:48,624
I'm testing the new machine.

843
00:41:50,265 --> 00:41:51,445
- Get to work.
- Okay.

844
00:41:52,144 --> 00:41:52,865
Go get changed.

845
00:41:56,104 --> 00:41:57,624
I've already consulted Mr. Qi.

846
00:41:58,305 --> 00:41:59,825
According to the current test results,

847
00:42:00,305 --> 00:42:03,104
if not reconstructed, it could last
seven or eight years without issue.

848
00:42:03,385 --> 00:42:04,865
But it's hard to say after ten years.

849
00:42:05,584 --> 00:42:06,224
Moreover,

850
00:42:06,465 --> 00:42:08,704
the risk of problems
increases year by year.

851
00:42:12,305 --> 00:42:13,745
Then demolish and rebuild it all.

852
00:42:16,745 --> 00:42:17,624
Are you sure?

853
00:42:19,265 --> 00:42:19,945
I am.

854
00:42:22,425 --> 00:42:23,224
Are you sure?

855
00:42:25,385 --> 00:42:26,184
What do you mean?

856
00:42:28,624 --> 00:42:29,624
Is there enough time?

857
00:42:30,224 --> 00:42:31,704
I've already contacted Mr. Zhao

858
00:42:32,144 --> 00:42:34,745
and reported the detailed situation.

859
00:42:35,265 --> 00:42:36,785
He also agreed to help us coordinate.

860
00:42:36,945 --> 00:42:38,985
A city model construction team
will be sent over.

861
00:42:40,385 --> 00:42:40,885
Yu,

862
00:42:41,265 --> 00:42:42,104
get ready

863
00:42:42,544 --> 00:42:44,865
and work out
an implementation plan with them.

864
00:42:51,345 --> 00:42:51,945
Yu,

865
00:42:52,785 --> 00:42:53,584
what's on your mind?

866
00:42:55,604 --> 00:42:57,385
I was thinking if my master were alive,

867
00:42:58,465 --> 00:42:59,345
what would he think?

868
00:43:06,280 --> 00:43:10,990
♪Gently holding your face♪

869
00:43:13,340 --> 00:43:18,588
♪To dry the tears from your eyes♪

870
00:43:20,148 --> 00:43:25,341
♪My heart will always be yours♪

871
00:43:27,156 --> 00:43:32,492
♪Tell me you'll never be alone again♪

872
00:43:34,120 --> 00:43:38,108
♪Gazing deep into your eyes♪

873
00:43:41,028 --> 00:43:46,397
♪No further words are needed♪

874
00:43:48,033 --> 00:43:53,238
♪Tightly holding your hand♪

875
00:43:54,972 --> 00:44:00,332
♪The warmth has never changed♪

876
00:44:01,448 --> 00:44:04,556
♪We share the joy♪

877
00:44:04,884 --> 00:44:08,108
♪We share the pain♪

878
00:44:08,362 --> 00:44:13,933
♪We hold the same hope deep inside♪

879
00:44:15,373 --> 00:44:18,372
♪We brave the storm♪

880
00:44:18,892 --> 00:44:21,884
♪We share the quest♪

881
00:44:22,325 --> 00:44:28,268
♪We cherish this love we share♪

882
00:44:31,458 --> 00:44:36,514
♪Whether we've ever met before♪

883
00:44:38,419 --> 00:44:43,829
♪Be it near or far away♪

884
00:44:45,420 --> 00:44:50,603
♪My heartfelt wish for you♪

885
00:44:52,387 --> 00:44:57,517
♪Is for your peace and happiness♪

886
00:44:58,824 --> 00:45:01,994
♪We share the joy♪

887
00:45:02,252 --> 00:45:05,320
♪We share the pain♪

888
00:45:05,744 --> 00:45:11,967
♪We hold the same hope deep inside♪

889
00:45:12,567 --> 00:45:15,630
♪We brave the storm♪

890
